# SEO regression test suite — file-scoped guidance

You are touching code that is covered by the four-layer SEO regression test
suite. Read these before changing anything:

- [tests/seo/README.md](mdc:tests/seo/README.md) — full guide (commands,
  allowlist, snapshot review checklist, layout)
- [docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-25-seo-regression-suite-design.md](mdc:docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-25-seo-regression-suite-design.md) — design rationale and invariant definitions
- [tests/seo/__known-issues__.json](mdc:tests/seo/__known-issues__.json) — allowlist of pre-existing audit findings

## When you change a page or component under `artifacts/*/src/pages/` or `artifacts/*/src/components/`

1. Build the dist artifacts the way CI does:
   ```
   pnpm --filter @workspace/nexfortis run build
   pnpm --filter @workspace/qb-portal exec vite build --config vite.config.ts
   ```
2. Run `pnpm test:seo`. It MUST pass.
3. If `test:seo:snapshots` reports a diff:
   - Walk the snapshot diff review checklist in `tests/seo/README.md`.
   - If every diff is the intended consequence of your change, run
     `pnpm test:seo:update` and re-run `pnpm test:seo`.
   - If any diff is unexpected, investigate before updating.
4. If your change fixes a Phase 2 audit issue, remove the corresponding entry
   from `tests/seo/__known-issues__.json` in the same PR. Confirm
   `pnpm test:seo:invariants` still passes after removal.

## When you change `tests/seo/lib/*` or `scripts/seo-verification/*`

This is test infrastructure. Do not modify it as part of an audit fix PR. If
the suite genuinely needs new helper functionality, open a separate
`feat(seo-tests):` PR for it.

## When you change `__known-issues__.json`

Each entry must keep this exact shape:

```json
{
  "site": "nexfortis" | "qb-portal",
  "route": "/some/path",
  "current": "<observed failing value>",
  "expected": "<value the invariant requires>",
  "issue": "<audit ID like C1, I5, M2>",
  "note": "<short explanation>"
}
```

Never add new entries to silence a violation introduced by your own change —
fix the violation instead. Adding entries is reserved for seeding pre-existing
audit findings.

## When you touch routes that affect the sitemap

Both sites publish a `sitemap.xml`. The committed
[artifacts/qb-portal/public/sitemap.xml](mdc:artifacts/qb-portal/public/sitemap.xml)
is canonical for qb-portal (vite copies it verbatim into dist). If you add or
remove routes, update both the sitemap and the snapshots in
`tests/seo/__snapshots__/<site>/sitemap.snap.json`.
